body:
One location in UVM gives "Unsupported: waiting on local event variables"

```
  virtual task wait_for_relevant();
    event e;
    wait_rel_default = 1;
    if (is_rel_default != wait_rel_default)
      uvm_report_fatal("RELMSM",
        "is_relevant() was implemented without defining wait_for_relevant()", UVM_NONE);
     @e;  // <- %Error-UNSUPPORTED: t/t_uvm_pkg_todo.vh:20247:5: Unsupported: waiting on local event variables
  endtask
```

This blocks UVM post-elaboration.

We should fix this, or perhaps as there's only one we can hack the uvm-verilator code base to work around it.

Note @kbieganski et al
